Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
placePadIO(25.10)                                            placePadIO(25.10)

Name
       placePadIO - Places the I/O pads evenly from one row to multiple rows

Syntax
        placePadIO

       [-help]

       [-rows <numOfRow>]

       [-maxIOHeight]

       Places  the  I/O pads evenly from one row to multiple rows. You can use
       this command after design initialization when the Innovus software  au-
       tomatically places the I/O pads in one row.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each placePadIO parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man placePadIO.

       -rows <numOfRows>
              Specifies the number of I/O rows needed for the placement.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -maxIOHeight
              Specifies the maximum height used to calculate the head box.  By
              default, this command uses the minimum height.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command places I/O pads in two I/O rows:

                placePadIO -row 2

Related Information
              * placePIO

              * placeAIO

              * setIoRowMargin

